			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: This NPC cannot be charmed?<a name="44419"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 5 04 9:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The only time you cannot charm something is if it is no-charm flagged, and says &quot;This NPC cannot be charmed.&quot; or if it is too high a level and says &quot;This NPC cannot be charmed with this spell.&quot; The latter means a higher level spell or song may work.
<br />

<br />
The 2nd line would read &quot;Mob_00 resisted your Solon's Song of Charming&quot; &lt;- which simply means it is resisted for any reason. Getting JUST this message means you COULD land the spell, given enough time or debuffs, etc.
<br />

<br />
This same logic applies to slows, snares, mezzes, etc. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://eq.uberage.com/" target="nw">Hakujin</a> - Bertoxxulous</span></td>
